Uinael, how long was it since you raided without a cleric epic ? On our average raids we have 3 clerics (no epics) and between 18 to 24 people raid force. With this we do Planes, ToV, some named mobs, epics  etc etc. Not counting wipes and the following CR, people tend to die every now and then. A rezz still costs 600mana. Its a big pain to keep the raid going when you need to spend a lot of mana on rezzes.<br>
<br>
Our first cleric epic piece will make a huge difference for us, while the following cleric epics will only provide redundancy.<br>
<br>
Our guild could probably live with a FCFS on Ragefire, but we would rather have a list to keep things civil. What Belmonte posted could work, Id think most people could wait at least 4 hours before bumping the cleric on top of the list.<br>
<br>
Leaving that behind, Im more interested in this : Did anyone actually see/take down the &quot;killable Zordac/Ragefire&quot; yet ? He should have popped by now if the spawn is working. I dont really care if it was &quot;taken&quot; out of turn or anything like that, would just be nice to know if its working atm.<br>
